description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking to recruit experienced Healthcare Assistants to join a Covid-19 Screening team located at Queen Alexandra Hospital in Portsmouth on a fixed term basis. This is a newly established team that primarily facilitates the Covid screening for pre elective patients and staff working under the direction of a RN Covid Coordinator. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service is a flexible and responsive provision, currently open 7 days a week, 365 days a year. Extended hours may be required on occasion by prior agreement. There is no night-time working required for this post.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;hands on patient facing role&lt;/strong&gt; therefore ideally you will have recent NHS experience, work great as part of a team and be looking for an opportunity to build on your healthcare knowledge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we can offer;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contracts available between 20-37.5 hrs per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive pay rates of pay&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bespoke induction and training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff benefit packages&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your primary responsibilities will be:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Meet and greet patients and staff that require testing, ensuring you have checked their personal details against the information provided and adhered to all trust data protection policies and procedures&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using the safety equipment and PPE provided ensure all tests are carried out effectively&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make sure test are appropriately sealed and labelled sending them in accordance to Trust guidance in a timely manner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Follow all infection control protocols ensuring the safety of yourself, colleagues and patients at all times&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note due the large amount of applicants, we cannot directly contact you if your application is unsuccessful.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date 24/11/2020&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
